article.headline: Oregon 70, Drake 40
article.story:
EUGENE, Ore. (AP) -- Reserve guard Cicely Oaks hit 10-of-10 free
throws on her way to a career-high 15 points, leading Oregon to a
70-40 victory over Drake on Monday.

Brandi Davis added a dozen points off the bench for the Ducks
(5-1), who shot 49 percent and got at least two points from all 12
of their players.

Jill Martin and Jane Horkey scored eight points apiece for Drake
(2-2), which shot 22 percent from the field and made 2-of-19
attempts from 3-point range.

Oaks had 11 points to lead the Ducks to a 35-19 halftime
advantage.

The Ducks never trailed, pulling away from an early 7-7 tie with
a 14-0 run. The Bulldogs connected on just two field goals in the
final 14:54 of the first half.

Oaks hit two free throws to give the Ducks a 51-27 edge midway
through the second half, and the Ducks scored the final 11 points
of the game to take their biggest lead.

The Oregon defense forced the Bulldogs into 20 turnovers. Duck
opponents are averaging 44.3 points per game this season and
shooting 27.9 percent from the field.
